		<div class="comment-content">
			
			<p>@<a href="#c3599043" rel="nofollow">Hambriq</a>: You&#8217;re right. But having once been subjected to medical battery, I get a little wound up about non-consent issues in general. <img src='http://s0.wp.com/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif?m=1129645325g' alt=':)' class='wp-smiley' /> </p>
<p>One of the reasons I like my current doctor and ob/gyn is that both explain in excruciating detail what&#8217;s going to happen next or why I need to do X or what all the side effects are going to be. If I had a doctor who just handed me a script without telling me why or what for or the full 411 (even after I asked), I honestly probably wouldn&#8217;t take it. I certainly wouldn&#8217;t go back to that doctor.</p>
