			<p>@<a href="#c3599522" rel="nofollow">AtOurGates</a>: I meant to add, my dad was in a similar position, except that he was lucky enough to have a doctor who didn&#8217;t try to sell him on surgery.  He was having a lot of hip pain and walking was getting to be a problem, so he went and asked a highly-rated orthopedic surgeon about a hip replacement.  The surgeon didn&#8217;t give him a yes-or-no answer, instead asking &#8220;What do YOU want to do?&#8221;  In other words, if Dad demanded a hip replacement, the doc would do it, but he wasn&#8217;t going to push it on him.</p>
